WEBVTT

00:00:00.090 --> 00:00:01.820
<v Instructor>So now let's talk about a few exam tips</v>

00:00:01.820 --> 00:00:04.610
that I can give you before you go into the exam.

00:00:04.610 --> 00:00:07.850
So this is AWS, so practice makes perfect.

00:00:07.850 --> 00:00:09.410
I would recommend, if you can,

00:00:09.410 --> 00:00:11.190
to follow this hands-on in this course

00:00:11.190 --> 00:00:12.780
if you are new to AWS,

00:00:12.780 --> 00:00:14.410
and don't rush before getting to the exam,

00:00:14.410 --> 00:00:16.920
make sure you really understand what services do

00:00:16.920 --> 00:00:18.150
and how they work.

00:00:18.150 --> 00:00:20.300
Overall, the more you can practice the better,

00:00:20.300 --> 00:00:22.740
and the more confident you will feel for the exam.

00:00:22.740 --> 00:00:24.790
The exam does recommend you have six month or more

00:00:24.790 --> 00:00:25.659
of hands-on experience,

00:00:25.659 --> 00:00:27.650
but hopefully, in this course,

00:00:27.650 --> 00:00:29.640
by following the hands-on, if you did them,

00:00:29.640 --> 00:00:32.320
you will have gained a lot of experience already.

00:00:32.320 --> 00:00:34.620
And finally, remember, practice makes perfect.

00:00:34.620 --> 00:00:36.010
If you feel overwhelmed

00:00:36.010 --> 00:00:37.440
by the amount of knowledge we learned,

00:00:37.440 --> 00:00:40.810
so more than 40 services in 10 hours,

00:00:40.810 --> 00:00:42.980
maybe you will go through it one more time,

00:00:42.980 --> 00:00:45.190
just to solidify these concepts into your head.

00:00:45.190 --> 00:00:47.530
It could be a lot to take at once.

00:00:47.530 --> 00:00:50.200
So let's talk about the exam content and question types.

00:00:50.200 --> 00:00:52.260
So there are two types of question on the exam.

00:00:52.260 --> 00:00:53.660
The first one is a multiple choice,

00:00:53.660 --> 00:00:55.227
that means that you have one correct answer

00:00:55.227 --> 00:00:57.360
and three incorrect responses.

00:00:57.360 --> 00:00:58.917
So it will look like this, for example,

00:00:58.917 --> 00:01:01.250
"Which AWS service does rock,"

00:01:01.250 --> 00:01:02.530
and you have option one, option two,

00:01:02.530 --> 00:01:03.990
option three, and option four.

00:01:03.990 --> 00:01:05.090
And you can see it's a circle,

00:01:05.090 --> 00:01:07.810
so you can only choose one of these four options.

00:01:07.810 --> 00:01:09.260
Then you have multiple responses,

00:01:09.260 --> 00:01:11.100
where you have two or more correct responses,

00:01:11.100 --> 00:01:13.050
out of five or more options.

00:01:13.050 --> 00:01:16.760
And the exam software, you have to be very careful,

00:01:16.760 --> 00:01:19.160
does not check if you have selected

00:01:19.160 --> 00:01:20.920
the right number of answers.

00:01:20.920 --> 00:01:23.820
So for example, if the question is "Blabla questions,

00:01:23.820 --> 00:01:25.450
and then select two,"

00:01:25.450 --> 00:01:26.560
then it will give you option one,

00:01:26.560 --> 00:01:28.320
two, three, four, and five,

00:01:28.320 --> 00:01:30.510
and you should absolutely select two.

00:01:30.510 --> 00:01:33.010
But if you select one or if you select three,

00:01:33.010 --> 00:01:34.960
the exam software will not complain about it.

00:01:34.960 --> 00:01:37.010
So be very careful in these type of questions

00:01:37.010 --> 00:01:38.900
to really tic the number of boxes

00:01:38.900 --> 00:01:41.020
that correspond to how many answers you should select,

00:01:41.020 --> 00:01:42.197
based on the question,

00:01:42.197 --> 00:01:45.140
and the question will tell you how many questions,

00:01:45.140 --> 00:01:47.170
responses, should select.

00:01:47.170 --> 00:01:48.720
Always try to answer the question.

00:01:48.720 --> 00:01:50.440
That means that if you don't answer a question,

00:01:50.440 --> 00:01:52.330
it will be considered as incorrect.

00:01:52.330 --> 00:01:55.540
And if you have a wrong answer, you're not penalized.

00:01:55.540 --> 00:01:58.780
So no matter what, try to guess the answer.

00:01:58.780 --> 00:02:01.610
And finally, if you need to review a question for later,

00:02:01.610 --> 00:02:04.130
because maybe you don't know the answer right now,

00:02:04.130 --> 00:02:05.500
maybe it'll come back to you later,

00:02:05.500 --> 00:02:06.400
or maybe you're unsure

00:02:06.400 --> 00:02:08.320
about a question answer that you've done,

00:02:08.320 --> 00:02:10.630
you can flag it so you can answer it or not,

00:02:10.630 --> 00:02:11.880
and then flag it.

00:02:11.880 --> 00:02:14.220
And then when you're done answering all questions,

00:02:14.220 --> 00:02:15.800
you will have a flag screen.

00:02:15.800 --> 00:02:16.633
And on that screen,

00:02:16.633 --> 00:02:18.280
you can go back to all the questions that you've flagged

00:02:18.280 --> 00:02:20.260
or any other question for that matter.

00:02:20.260 --> 00:02:21.093
But with this,

00:02:21.093 --> 00:02:21.926
you can go back quickly to the question

00:02:21.926 --> 00:02:23.780
that you've flagged for maybe answering them

00:02:23.780 --> 00:02:26.480
or double checking your answer, these kinds of things.

00:02:27.610 --> 00:02:29.330
Now, for the question themselves,

00:02:29.330 --> 00:02:31.170
you should proceed by elimination.

00:02:31.170 --> 00:02:32.140
So most questions,

00:02:32.140 --> 00:02:33.740
as we've seen in the sample questions,

00:02:33.740 --> 00:02:36.580
are going to be high-level pick-a-service questions.

00:02:36.580 --> 00:02:39.650
So rule out the answers that you know for sure are wrong,

00:02:39.650 --> 00:02:40.882
and for the remaining answers,

00:02:40.882 --> 00:02:43.800
understand the one which makes the most sense.

00:02:43.800 --> 00:02:46.010
There are very few trick questions

00:02:46.010 --> 00:02:49.430
at the Cloud Practitioner level and the Associate level,

00:02:49.430 --> 00:02:51.260
so don't overthink it.

00:02:51.260 --> 00:02:53.860
If a solution seems feasible, but highly complicated,

00:02:53.860 --> 00:02:56.030
it's probably going to be wrong, okay?

00:02:56.030 --> 00:02:58.020
Think simple, follow your intuition,

00:02:58.020 --> 00:02:59.430
and you should be all right.

00:02:59.430 --> 00:03:00.300
Now, it is good for you,

00:03:00.300 --> 00:03:02.550
if you want to learn a bit more about AWS,

00:03:02.550 --> 00:03:04.570
to read each service's overview.

00:03:04.570 --> 00:03:06.800
So we've seen about 40 services in this course,

00:03:06.800 --> 00:03:07.633
so for example,

00:03:07.633 --> 00:03:09.190
if you wanted to look at the overview of S3,

00:03:09.190 --> 00:03:12.020
you will go to this URL and see what S3 can do.

00:03:12.020 --> 00:03:13.900
This could be really helpful because, again,

00:03:13.900 --> 00:03:15.700
these overviews will represent

00:03:15.700 --> 00:03:18.380
a lot of the questions asked at the exam,

00:03:18.380 --> 00:03:19.930
and by seeing the overview,

00:03:19.930 --> 00:03:23.340
you will confirm your understanding of a service.

00:03:23.340 --> 00:03:25.560
Finally, if you wanna go one step further,

00:03:25.560 --> 00:03:27.940
get into the AWS Community,

00:03:27.940 --> 00:03:29.990
that means helping and discussing with other people,

00:03:29.990 --> 00:03:32.040
especially in the course Q&A,

00:03:32.040 --> 00:03:34.840
review people's questions in the Q&A

00:03:34.840 --> 00:03:36.950
and try to answer them to confirm

00:03:36.950 --> 00:03:38.700
that you understand things correctly.

00:03:38.700 --> 00:03:42.160
And finally, do the practice exam in this section.

00:03:42.160 --> 00:03:44.150
And if you're looking for even more practice,

00:03:44.150 --> 00:03:46.360
then you can buy more practice exams from me

00:03:46.360 --> 00:03:49.320
from my dedicated practice exam course.

00:03:49.320 --> 00:03:50.690
You can read forums online,

00:03:50.690 --> 00:03:52.300
you can read online blogs,

00:03:52.300 --> 00:03:54.680
and if you want to really get into the community,

00:03:54.680 --> 00:03:56.090
you can attend local meetups

00:03:56.090 --> 00:03:58.280
and discuss with other AWS engineers.

00:03:58.280 --> 00:04:01.180
Finally, if you're really, really interested into AWS,

00:04:01.180 --> 00:04:03.410
watch the reinvent videos on YouTube.

00:04:03.410 --> 00:04:06.177
The reinvent is the conference of AWS.

00:04:07.210 --> 00:04:08.417
One question I get all the time is,

00:04:08.417 --> 00:04:10.090
"How will the exam work?"

00:04:10.090 --> 00:04:12.850
So you will have to register online at this URL,

00:04:12.850 --> 00:04:16.060
and the fee for this exam is going to be 100 U.S dollars.

00:04:16.060 --> 00:04:18.290
You need to provide two identity documents,

00:04:18.290 --> 00:04:20.000
so your ID, your credit card,

00:04:20.000 --> 00:04:21.469
and all of this will be in the details

00:04:21.469 --> 00:04:25.230
of an email sent to you once you register for the exam.

00:04:25.230 --> 00:04:27.090
And you're not allowed to take any notes,

00:04:27.090 --> 00:04:28.190
you're not allowed to use any pen,

00:04:28.190 --> 00:04:29.750
and you're not allowed to speak.

00:04:29.750 --> 00:04:31.290
You will have 65 questions

00:04:31.290 --> 00:04:33.860
that will be asked of you in 90 minutes.

00:04:33.860 --> 00:04:34.930
And at the end,

00:04:34.930 --> 00:04:37.630
you can optionally review all the questions and answers.

00:04:37.630 --> 00:04:38.490
And as you go along,

00:04:38.490 --> 00:04:40.050
you can flag the questions

00:04:40.050 --> 00:04:41.650
that you think are difficult for you

00:04:41.650 --> 00:04:43.880
to review them at the end, as well.

00:04:43.880 --> 00:04:45.380
So when you submit the exam,

00:04:45.380 --> 00:04:47.690
you will know right away if you've passed or failed,

00:04:47.690 --> 00:04:49.800
if you passed it says congratulation pass.

00:04:49.800 --> 00:04:51.670
If you fail, it will say fail.

00:04:51.670 --> 00:04:53.810
You will not know which answers are right or wrong,

00:04:53.810 --> 00:04:55.000
this is intended,

00:04:55.000 --> 00:04:57.870
and you will know your overall score only a few days later,

00:04:57.870 --> 00:04:59.980
you will have received an email notification.

00:04:59.980 --> 00:05:02.020
It can take sometimes up to five days,

00:05:02.020 --> 00:05:03.890
but normally two days.

00:05:03.890 --> 00:05:05.340
And then to pass this exam,

00:05:05.340 --> 00:05:08.600
as I said, you need a score of 700 out of 1,000.

00:05:08.600 --> 00:05:11.330
And if you happen to fail, which I don't wish you do,

00:05:11.330 --> 00:05:14.290
then you can retake the exam again after 14 days.

00:05:14.290 --> 00:05:16.860
So that's it, thank you so much for learning with me.

00:05:16.860 --> 00:05:18.680
I wish you the best for your certification.

00:05:18.680 --> 00:05:20.753
Happy learning and good luck.